# CODEOWNERS — default reviewers for pull requests
# Docs: https://docs.github.com/en/repositories/managing-your-repositorys-settings-and-features/customizing-your-repository/about-code-owners
#
# Each line defines a file pattern and the GitHub users/teams required to review
# changes to matching files. Later rules take precedence over earlier ones.
#
# Pair with branch-protection rule "Require review from Code Owners" on `main`
# for this to actually block merge — CODEOWNERS alone only auto-assigns the
# review request.

# Release-time touchpoints: every release-please PR edits these, so requesting
# @gerchowl as reviewer puts a human-in-the-loop signoff on every release.
# The release-reviewer checklist (release-please-config.json pull-request-header)
# includes a visual-inspection item that requires opening the latest catalog-
# previews / visual-regression run artifacts before approving.
CHANGELOG.md                          @gerchowl
.release-please-manifest.json         @gerchowl
release-please-config.json            @gerchowl

# Visual catalog: every change to TOMLs or vis adapters can shift the rendered
# look. CODEOWNERS here ties review to the human who can eyeball the artifact
# uploaded by catalog-previews / visual-regression workflows.
src/pymat/data/**                     @gerchowl
src/pymat/vis/**                      @gerchowl
tests/test_visual_regression.py       @gerchowl
tests/test_substrate_repros.py        @gerchowl
tests/visual_render.html              @gerchowl
scripts/generate_previews.py          @gerchowl
.github/workflows/catalog-previews.yml @gerchowl
.github/workflows/visual-regression.yml @gerchowl
